00:14:17,820 --> 00:14:20,280
Did I just say, "lf I were a guy"?

266
00:14:21,620 --> 00:14:23,520
You don't need him to propose to you.

267
00:14:23,570 --> 00:14:24,940
Maybe you could propose to him.

268
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:27,180
Oh, I don't know.

269
00:14:27,180 --> 00:14:29,060
I don't know. Isn't that a little desperate?

270
00:14:29,110 --> 00:14:30,730
I proposed to Chandler.

271
00:14:34,850 --> 00:14:36,570
All right, moving on.

272
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:38,800
I don't think it was desperate.

273
00:14:38,850 --> 00:14:39,930
It was amazing.

274
00:14:39,980 --> 00:14:40,850
Thank you.

275
00:14:41,170 --> 00:14:43,180
Well, do you think I should propose?

276
00:14:43,690 --> 00:14:45,430
I think it could be kind of great.

277
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:46,320
Absolutely.

278
00:14:46,370 --> 00:14:47,680
You'll love the feeling.

279
00:14:47,730 --> 00:14:48,830
There's nothing like it.

280
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:54,880
Okay. Okay. So how should I do it?

281
00:14:54,930 --> 00:14:57,100
How about at a game on the big screen?

282
00:14:57,980 --> 00:15:00,080
How about at a Foot Locker?

283
00:15:01,900 --> 00:15:04,040
What? What, he obviously thinks

284
00:15:04,090 --> 00:15:06,280
that's a nice way to be proposed to.

285
00:15:06,330 --> 00:15:08,180
Plus, he'd never suspect it.

286
00:15:08,230 --> 00:15:09,610
Yeah, that does make sense.

287
00:15:10,060 --> 00:15:12,400
Okay, now, would you two like that?

288
00:15:12,450 --> 00:15:13,500
Sounds good to me.

289
00:15:13,870 --> 00:15:15,890
But what would a guy think?

290
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:21,250
- Nana's on the phone. - Wow.

291
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:22,560
That's interesting,

292
00:15:22,610 --> 00:15:24,640
since she died seven years ago.

293
00:15:25,490 --> 00:15:26,770
She did?

294
00:15:27,470 --> 00:15:29,420
Who got her condo in Boca?

295
00:15:30,710 --> 00:15:31,720
Hello?

296
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:34,470
It's our nanny.

297
00:15:35,470 --> 00:15:36,480
Hi.

298
00:15:36,940 --> 00:15:41,420
Oh, God, I hope you feel better. Okay. Bye.

299
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:43,560
That's Molly. She's sick.

300
00:15:43,610 --> 00:15:44,760
Can you watch Emma today?

301
00:15:44,810 --> 00:15:46,940
I can't. I have back-to-back classes.

302
00:15:46,990 --> 00:15:48,400
Did Molly say what she had?

303
00:15:48,450 --> 00:15:50,100
Because my throat's been hurting.

304
00:15:50,150 --> 00:15:51,560
Menstrual cramps.

305
00:15:53,820 --> 00:15:55,680
I don't think that's what this is.

306
00:15:57,380 --> 00:15:59,030
Can any of you watch Emma?

307
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:00,290
No, I'm sorry, sweetie.

308
00:16:00,340 --> 00:16:02,830
No, I've got work, and then I'm proposing.

309
00:16:03,620 --> 00:16:05,800
Great. Shoot. What am I gonna do?

310
00:16:05,980 --> 00:16:07,460
Well, I could do it.

311
00:16:08,180 --> 00:16:09,220
Well, actually....

312
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:11,090
Can I talk to you for a second?

313
00:16:13,180 --> 00:16:16,380
I do not want her babysitting our child.

314
00:16:16,430 --> 00:16:17,140
Why not?

315
00:16:17,190 --> 00:16:19,620
For one thing, she keeps calling her Ella.

316
00:16:19,990 --> 00:16:22,170
Ella's a nice name.

317
00:16:22,220 --> 00:16:23,640
Fine, we'll call the next one Ella.

318
00:16:23,690 --> 00:16:25,380
- The next one? - Okay.

319
00:16:27,160 --> 00:16:30,190
I don't want her watching our baby.

320
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:33,450
Ross, I am trying to help her become a better person.

321
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:35,440
This is a huge breakthrough for her.

322
00:16:35,490 --> 00:16:37,390
She just offered to do something

323
00:16:37,390 --> 00:16:38,740
for another human being.

324
00:16:39,730 --> 00:16:41,320
You know, I don't know.

325
00:16:41,370 --> 00:16:42,380
Ross, I'm telling you...

326
00:16:42,430 --> 00:16:46,630
...she's giving up getting her eyebrows shaped to do this, all right?

327
00:16:46,680 --> 00:16:47,770
Do you understand

328
00:16:47,770 --> 00:16:50,130
how important that is in our world?

329
00:16:51,700 --> 00:16:54,790
Listen, I couldn't help but overhear,

330
00:16:55,140 --> 00:16:56,750
because I was trying to.

331
00:16:58,130 --> 00:16:59,770
Listen, let me do this.

332
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:01,340
I really want to help you guys out.

333
00:17:01,390 --> 00:17:04,130
And plus, Rachel's been so wonderful to me.

334
00:17:07,030 --> 00:17:09,530
- Absolutely. - Oh, great!

335
00:17:10,070 --> 00:17:11,470
So how much does it pay?

336
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:19,530
Hi,Joe.

337
00:17:19,530 --> 00:17:20,770
How's the second draft of the letter coming?

338
00:17:20,820 --> 00:17:21,710
Great. I'm finished.

339
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:23,400
In fact, I just dropped it off at the agency.

340
00:17:26,300 --> 00:17:28,040
- You dropped it off? - Yeah.

341
00:17:28,090 --> 00:17:29,090
Can we read it?

342
00:17:29,140 --> 00:17:30,760
Can you print out another copy?

343
00:17:30,810 --> 00:17:32,460
No can do, <i>amigo.</i>

344
00:17:33,970 --> 00:17:35,290
No, I didn't use the computer.

345
00:17:35,340 --> 00:17:37,530
It felt more personal to handwrite it.

346
00:17:38,730 --> 00:17:41,000
- You handwrote it? - Yeah, and don't worry.

347
00:17:41,050 --> 00:17:43,340
I didn't try to sound smart at all.

348
00:17:44,410 --> 00:17:45,740
See you later.

349
00:17:46,190 --> 00:17:47,590
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

350
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:50,110
That letter is gonna go in our file.

351
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:51,850
We're never gonna get a kid.

352
00:17:51,900 --> 00:17:53,830
We're gonna be one of those old couples...

353
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:57,020
...that collects orchids or has a lot of birds.

354
00:17:57,670 --> 00:17:59,820
It's okay. You know what?

355
00:17:59,870 --> 00:18:01,890
I will just call the agency

356
00:18:01,940 --> 00:18:03,630
and tell them to throw out the letter.

357
00:18:03,680 --> 00:18:04,760
Okay, good.

358
00:18:05,850 --> 00:18:07,380
Hello, this is Chandler Bing.

359
00:18:07,430 --> 00:18:09,120
Someone just dropped off

360
00:18:09,170 --> 00:18:11,120
a handwritten recommendation letter and....

361
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:18,060
Okay.

362
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:21,370
Thank you. Goodbye.

363
00:18:21,950 --> 00:18:24,160
We're screwed, aren't we?

364
00:18:24,210 --> 00:18:24,840
You know what?

365
00:18:24,890 --> 00:18:26,540
Just tell me on the way to the bird store.

366
00:18:28,430 --> 00:18:30,110
- They loved it. - What?

367
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,660
They thought it was very smart of us

368
00:18:31,710 --> 00:18:33,970
to have a child write the letter.

369
00:18:35,330 --> 00:18:37,350
They thought Joey was a child?

370
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:40,300
She guessed 8, 9, based on his drawings.

371
00:18:43,590 --> 00:18:46,320
- Hi. - Hey, what'd you guys do today?

372
00:18:46,370 --> 00:18:48,030
Ella wanted to go out,

373
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:51,140
so we went shopping and got some sushi.

374
00:18:51,860 --> 00:18:54,370
- That sounds like fun. - Yeah, not really.

375
00:18:55,130 --> 00:18:56,540
Babies are dull.

376
00:18:58,420 --> 00:19:02,700
- Hey. Hi, how's my girl? - I'm fine.

377
00:19:03,270 --> 00:19:05,920
And I got you a present

378
00:19:05,970 --> 00:19:07,170
for letting me stay with you.

379
00:19:08,650 --> 00:19:10,090
- Ready? - Yeah.

380
00:19:14,310 --> 00:19:15,960
You pierced her ears?

381
00:19:16,010 --> 00:19:18,870
Doesn't it make her nose look smaller?

382
00:19:24,630 --> 00:19:27,170
You pierced her ears?

383
00:19:27,220 --> 00:19:29,300
How could you do this without telling me?

384
00:19:29,350 --> 00:19:30,640
If I had told you,

385
00:19:30,690 --> 00:19:32,560
then it wouldn't have been a surprise, now would it?

386
00:19:33,760 --> 00:19:35,570
I think she looks cute.

387
00:19:36,390 --> 00:19:37,700
But I am wrong.

388
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:41,190
Oh, my God. Oh, my God. Here comes Ross.

389
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:43,820
He's gonna flip out.

390
00:19:44,050 --> 00:19:45,600
Why, did something happen

391
00:19:45,610 --> 00:19:46,320
to his falafel cart?

392
00:19:47,910 --> 00:19:49,640
- Hey, guys. - Ross!

393
00:19:49,780 --> 00:19:51,330
Hi, Emma.

394
00:19:51,330 --> 00:19:53,530
Why is she wearing her hat so low?

395
00:19:53,580 --> 00:19:54,790
She can barely see.

396
00:19:54,840 --> 00:19:56,460
I don't really want her to see.

397
00:19:58,460 --> 00:19:59,760
Why not?

398
00:19:59,810 --> 00:20:02,560
Because there are so many terrible sights in this world.

399
00:20:02,610 --> 00:20:05,930
Like war. Or that thing in Joey's refrigerator. Remember?

400
00:20:05,980 --> 00:20:08,580
It was in a milk carton, but it looked like meat?

401
00:20:10,210 --> 00:20:11,960
Come here.

402
00:20:12,500 --> 00:20:15,540
There she is. Hi.

403
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:19,690
- What? - Nothing.

404
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:22,710
Hi.

405
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:25,900
What--?

406
00:20:37,090 --> 00:20:39,170
Please tell me those are clip-ons!

407
00:20:39,820 --> 00:20:41,140
Oh, they're real.

408
00:20:41,790 --> 00:20:44,100
Did she do this to her?

409
00:20:44,150 --> 00:20:45,200
I told you

410
00:20:45,250 --> 00:20:46,590
we shouldn't have left Emma with her!

411
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:48,690
I know, I know. And you were right, Ross.

412
00:20:48,740 --> 00:20:50,790
Okay? You are so irresponsible!

413
00:20:50,840 --> 00:20:52,520
I am never letting you babysit again!

414
00:20:52,570 --> 00:20:54,840
You know what? This kid needs me, okay?

415
00:20:54,890 --> 00:20:57,300
She needs to have a cool, fun aunt.

416
00:20:57,350 --> 00:20:58,590
I'm a cool, fun aunt.

417
00:20:58,640 --> 00:20:59,770
Okay.

418
00:21:00,890 --> 00:21:03,750
Hey! Monica can be cool and fun

419
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:05,830
at organized indoor projects.

420
00:21:07,830 --> 00:21:10,410
All I wanted to do was help you

421
00:21:10,460 --> 00:21:12,250
try to figure out what to do with your life.

422
00:21:12,300 --> 00:21:13,740
This is how you repay me?

423
00:21:13,790 --> 00:21:15,280
I don't need you to help me.

424
00:21:15,330 --> 00:21:17,280
Because I already know what I'm gonna do with my life.

425
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:20,600
- Oh, yeah? Since when? - Since today.

426
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:26,520
I am going to be a baby stylist.

427
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:30,130
- What? - That's not a thing!

428
00:21:31,700 --> 00:21:33,270
Well, it should be.

429
00:21:33,470 --> 00:21:36,370
I'm gonna help babies learn how to accessorize...

430
00:21:36,420 --> 00:21:38,270
...what colors to wear,

431
00:21:38,270 --> 00:21:39,890
what clothes are slimming.

432
00:21:39,940 --> 00:21:41,680
Babies don't care if they're slim!

433
00:21:41,730 --> 00:21:43,300
Enter Amy.

434
00:21:44,710 --> 00:21:47,150
Amy, l-- I just-- I just wanna--

435
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:48,610
What? What are you gonna do?

436
00:21:50,220 --> 00:21:52,310
No more falafel for you!

437
00:22:05,380 --> 00:22:06,730
Great game, huh?

438
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,490
Why do you keep looking at the screen?

439
00:22:11,540 --> 00:22:13,740
I'm not. I'm praying.

440
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:16,480
Please let the Knicks win.

441
00:22:16,990 --> 00:22:18,400
Thank you, Thor.

442
00:22:19,930 --> 00:22:21,160
Where are you going?

443
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:22,660
I'm going to the bathroom.

444
00:22:22,980 --> 00:22:24,160
Well, I think you should wait.

445
00:22:24,210 --> 00:22:24,960
Why?

446
00:22:26,140 --> 00:22:28,130
Well, if you don't hold it in,

447
00:22:28,180 --> 00:22:30,140
you don't get all the nutrients.

448
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:33,820
<i>Knicks fans, please turn your attention</i>

449
00:22:33,870 --> 00:22:35,740
<i>to the big screen on the scoreboard.</i>

450
00:22:35,790 --> 00:22:38,980
<i>Someone has a special question to ask.</i>

451
00:22:41,620 --> 00:22:44,520
Mike Hannigan, will you marry me?

452
00:22:46,170 --> 00:22:50,060
<i>Get a load of this.</i> <i>She's proposing to him!</i>

453
00:22:50,110 --> 00:22:53,250
<i>Guess we know who wears</i> <i>the pants in that family.</i>

454
00:22:53,900 --> 00:22:56,110
Well, that's not very enlightened.

455
00:23:00,530 --> 00:23:02,910
Boo us? Boo you!

456
00:23:09,490 --> 00:23:13,120
Hello? Yeah, this is Joey Tribbiani.

457
00:23:13,560 --> 00:23:14,770
Oh, hi.

458
00:23:17,150 --> 00:23:19,130
Well, I'm glad you liked my letter.

459
00:23:21,010 --> 00:23:24,050
No, my mommy and daddy aren't home right now.

460
00:23:25,980 --> 00:23:27,480
Okay, bye-bye.

461
00:23:31,140 --> 00:23:32,400
She was nice.

462
00:23:34,110 --> 00:23:36,840
Joey, get Amy's bags. She is moving out.

463
00:23:38,950 --> 00:23:40,390
You're kicking me out?

464
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:42,950
You put holes in my baby's ears.

465
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:45,570
At least now people will know she's a girl!

466
00:23:48,030 --> 00:23:50,880
I can't believe I ever even tried to help you.

467
00:23:50,930 --> 00:23:53,220
- You are so beyond help! - You know what?

468
00:23:53,270 --> 00:23:56,610
Ever since I got here, you have been nothing but negative.

469
00:23:56,660 --> 00:23:58,090
- Excuse me? - You didn't want me...

470
00:23:58,140 --> 00:24:00,560
...to marry the old guy with the great apartment.

471
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:05,330
Then I tried to help your daughter de-emphasize her flaws...

472
00:24:05,940 --> 00:24:08,110
...and suddenly I'm the bad guy?

473
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:09,620
Joey, where are those bags?

474
00:24:09,670 --> 00:24:11,200
She has a lot of crap!

475
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:14,650
You know? When I moved in here,

476
00:24:14,650 --> 00:24:16,340
I thought, "This will be so great.

477
00:24:16,390 --> 00:24:19,610
Just us sisters back together again like when we were kids."

478
00:24:19,660 --> 00:24:21,670
Except without that stupid Jill.

479
00:24:22,990 --> 00:24:25,110
Who has gotten fat, by the way.

480
00:24:27,030 --> 00:24:28,260
Seriously?

481
00:24:28,930 --> 00:24:31,240
Mom said she gained, like, 15 pounds.

482
00:24:31,290 --> 00:24:33,560
- Hips or thighs? - Ass and face.

483
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:38,350
Oh, my God! I thought she was on Atkins.

484
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:40,320
She was. Carbs found her.

485
00:24:45,020 --> 00:24:47,460
See? This is what I wanted.

486
00:24:47,940 --> 00:24:50,420
Two sisters talking about real stuff.

487
00:24:53,840 --> 00:24:56,010
Oh, I can give you that.

488
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:58,270
- You can? - Yeah.

489
00:24:58,560 --> 00:25:01,560
I kept trying to make you a better person, but you're....

490
00:25:01,820 --> 00:25:04,830
You're already a pretty perfect version of what you are.

491
00:25:05,890 --> 00:25:07,570
Thank you.

492
00:25:08,310 --> 00:25:10,680
You gotta admit, Emma does look cute.

493
00:25:12,580 --> 00:25:14,160
Did you just say, "Emma"?

494
00:25:14,210 --> 00:25:15,780
Oh, I'm sorry. Ella.

495
00:25:22,630 --> 00:25:25,400
That woman didn't know what she was talking about, Mike.

496
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:27,570
Obviously, you have balls.

497
00:25:29,330 --> 00:25:31,210
Please, let's forget the whole thing.

498
00:25:31,260 --> 00:25:32,280
I would love it.

499
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:33,310
Consider it forgotten.

500
00:25:33,310 --> 00:25:34,170
Thank you.

501
00:25:35,240 --> 00:25:36,660
But just so you know....

502
00:25:37,070 --> 00:25:40,200
However and whenever you decide to propose,

503
00:25:40,250 --> 00:25:41,940
I promise I'll say yes.

504
00:25:43,120 --> 00:25:45,490
Whether, you know, it's at a basketball game...

505
00:25:45,540 --> 00:25:47,480
...or in skywriting...

506
00:25:47,530 --> 00:25:50,450
...or, you know, like some lame guy in a cheesy movie...

507
00:25:50,500 --> 00:25:52,030
...who hides it in the cake.

508
00:25:57,950 --> 00:25:59,750
It's in the cake, isn't it?

509
00:26:01,750 --> 00:26:04,750
Where else would lame Mr. No Balls hide it?

510
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:07,020
What's the matter with me?

511
00:26:07,070 --> 00:26:08,550
Why do I keep ruining this?

512
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,990
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

513
00:26:10,040 --> 00:26:11,000
No, it's my fault.

514
00:26:11,050 --> 00:26:13,810
I keep trying to propose in these stupid ways...

515
00:26:13,860 --> 00:26:15,370
...and I just wanna tell you I love you,

516
00:26:15,420 --> 00:26:17,680
and I wanna spend my life with you....

517
00:26:22,030 --> 00:26:23,450
I'm gonna do this now.

518
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:25,300
Oh, my God.

519
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:29,790
Phoebe, l--

520
00:26:29,840 --> 00:26:30,720
Wait. Oh, wait.

521
00:26:35,850 --> 00:26:36,790
Oh, no.

522
00:26:40,130 --> 00:26:41,270
Okay.

523
00:26:42,580 --> 00:26:43,990
Ready? Okay.

524
00:26:47,830 --> 00:26:50,390
Phoebe, I love you.

525
00:26:52,190 --> 00:26:53,510
There's no one else in the world

526
00:26:53,560 --> 00:26:55,780
I would ask to marry me three times.

527
00:26:58,130 --> 00:27:00,020
But I want to take care of you...

528
00:27:00,820 --> 00:27:02,180
...have babies with you...

529
00:27:03,580 --> 00:27:04,940
...and grow old with you.

530
00:27:07,790 --> 00:27:10,940
Phoebe Buffay, will you marry me?

531
00:27:11,950 --> 00:27:12,910
Yes.

532
00:27:20,010 --> 00:27:22,670
- I love you. - I love you more.

533
00:27:22,670 --> 00:27:23,980
Not possible.

534
00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:35,370
She's gonna be Mrs. No Balls!

535
00:27:42,100 --> 00:27:45,450
